{"key":"post-15856659","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15856659</id>\n<content>It's best to leave the cakes on foil.&amp;nbsp; The reason is that a small substrate can only support so many fruits.&amp;nbsp; If you interfere with the process, you might get a thousand pins, but then nearly all abort, leaving you with less product than following the tek.&amp;nbsp; Also, many cakes only pin on the bottom, but easily lift the cake out of their way as they grow.&amp;nbsp; Remember, a mushroom can move a 40 pound rock out of its way in the forest, so don't feel that a small brf cake is going to be an impediment.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>15856597</prev>\n<first>15855938</first>\n<last>15856659</last>\n<when>1330097493</when>\n<utime>02/24/12 05:31 PM</utime>\n</post>"}